commText: Sunday. Monday. Tuesday. And Mumbai Indians losing their opening game. The routine of an IPL calendar every year. It's their, I0$, 12th loss on the trot, and their last win in an opening encounter came in 2012. But remember, they also won 5 of the last 11 titles. All teams have now finished round one, and the action shifts to garden city tomorrow as RCB and Punjab Kings await their second game of the season. Jeers for Hardik Pandya, Mohit Sharma's revival, Umesh Yadav's final over, Sai-Rashid's spinning web....there will be lots of talking points from this game and do remember to check this space for all the spicy (news) and exclusive content. Until next time, cheers and goodbye from I1$and I2$. Feet up!!

Sai Sudharsan | Player of the Match: I feel even in the first innings it was slightly difficult and second innings because of the dew they were able to play a few shots, but we pulled off a great game today. I am just taking it as an extra opportunity to try and win a game for my team. After a few balls, I felt this is that kind of a wicket where you can go hard everywhere and wanted to build on the momentum. Too many great contributions in the second innings and I am actually shocked to be receiving this award. As a batter, I found it tough when they took the pace off and our bowlers executed really well today.

Shubman Gill | GT skipper: The way the boys held their nerves with dew coming in, it was outstanding. The way our spinners bowled made sure we are always in the game. It's all about holding your nerves. He (Sai Sudharsan) has been a revelation for us. We just wanted to build on the pressure and wait for them to make mistakes. The crowd is one thing, have always come whether it is a day game or a night game and shout out to all the fans who have come here to support us. I thought that was a good score, but we definitely left at least 15 runs there, it was hard to hit those short balls as the wicket got a bit slow towards the end.

Spencer Johnson: Absolutely incredible (feeling) to get the win in front of a full house is pretty special. Ashish Nehra told me to be calm, you are going to win the game. What worked well for me was the hard length and keeping calm and not panicking and sticking to what I do well. I have always wanted to play in India and the crowd was amazing. Sat next to Shubman in the bus on our way to the ground. He was calming me. We talked through the game. He is unbelievable as a young captain.
Most wickets vs MI in the IPL 33 - Dwayne Bravo 33 - Mohit Sharma 26 - Ravichandran Ashwin 25 - Yuzvendra Chahal 25 - Piyush Chawla 25 - Amit Mishra

Hardik Pandya | MI captain: Obviously we backed ourselves to chase those 42 runs but it was one of those days when we see the score quite less compared to what it could have been in five overs, I think we lost little bit of momentum there. It feels good to be back because this is one stadium where you can enjoy and feel the atmosphere quite lively and obviously the crowd was full and they got a good game as well. (On Tilak not taking the single vs Rashid) I think Tilak felt that that was a better idea at that point of time, I completely back him, not an issue, 13 games to go.
Mohit Sharma in death overs (17-20) in IPL since 2023 Balls: 97 Runs conceded: 132 Wickets: 14 Avg: 9.42 SR: 6.93 ER: 8.16 Dots: 34

23:20 local, 17:50 GMT: If yesterday's SRH game was all about those last 5 balls, today's was all about the last 6 overs. MI needed 48 from 36 with 7 wickets in hand, and none of the pundits could have written a script for what was to unfold. 11 dots 6 wickets. That is almost 3 overs full of dot balls. The best part about GT's win is that, almost all their bowlers played a part. Sai Kishore, Rashid. Spencer Johnson, Mohit Sharma and Umesh Yadav - each individual contributing during crucial junctures of the contest. It's one of those games for MI where they'll look back and think "I0$" After Kishan fell for nought in the opening over, Naman Dhir gave a glimpse of his fearless ball-striking and then a 77-run third wicket stand between Rohit and Brevis followed. After that heart-crushing loss in the IPL final last year and the events that followed, the victory shall feel a lot sweeter for the Titans. And it will sting quite a bit for Hardik Pandya. Let's see what he has to say....

Umesh Yadav to Shams Mulani, 1 run, Gujarat Titans win by 6 runs, it is their third win against Mumbai Indians at this venue as well. Shams Mulani pulls the short ball and it lands well short of the incoming Sai Kishore at fine leg. Game over!!

Umesh Yadav to Bumrah, 1 run, I0$ short of length outside off, Bumrah can only chop it into the off-side. That should be the game for GT. And Nehra is back to being busy and cheery on the sidelines...
Jasprit Bumrah, right handed bat, comes to the crease
9 needed from 2. And Umesh Yadav is on a hat-trick as well....

Umesh Yadav to Chawla, out Caught by Rashid Khan!! And now a catching practice to Rashid Khan at deep mid-wicket. Umesh Yadav goes bumper outside off and Chawla's pulled that flat and straight into the hands of the fielder. The crowd are loving every bit of this. Chawla c Rashid Khan b Umesh Yadav 0(1)
Umesh Yadav to Chawla, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Piyush Chawla, left handed bat, comes to the crease
9 needed from 3

Umesh Yadav to Hardik Pandya, out Caught by Rahul Tewatia!! The biggest roar from the crowd and a few boos follow as Hardik Pandya trudges back to the pavilion. It was the pacy short ball from Umesh Yadav and Pandya couldn't get the desired connection on the pull. Dragged it off the toe of the bat and offered catching practice to Tewatia at long-on. Pandya perhaps wanted to hit it more towards mid-wicket and gestures something similar before going back to the dugout. Hardik Pandya c Rahul Tewatia b Umesh Yadav 11(4) [4s-1 6s-1]
Umesh Yadav to Hardik Pandya, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
9 needed from 4

Umesh Yadav to Hardik Pandya, FOUR, Nehra doesn't want to look. He is walking away from the dugout. The length is short and there's enough width for Hardik Pandya to pounce and bash that along the ground through extra cover....

Umesh Yadav to Hardik Pandya, SIX, slow and banged in short outside off, Hardik Pandya has smoked that over extra cover. He perhaps knew what was coming and always had his weight on the back foot, picked the length early and packed it into the stands with an air of authority...
Umesh Yadav [2.0-0-19-0] is back into the attack
Shams Mulani, left handed bat, comes to the crease
19 needed from 6

Spencer Johnson to Gerald Coetzee, out Caught&Bowled!! Flags flying everywhere and the fans have gone crazy here in Ahmedabad. Spencer Johnson bowls short and Coetzee's pull finds a massive top-edge that swirls in the square leg area. The bowler calls for it and accepts it gleefully. What an over from the Australian quick. Last night we have seen a different story from another Australian quick in the penultimate over.... Gerald Coetzee c and b Spencer Johnson 1(3)
Spencer Johnson to Gerald Coetzee, THATS OUT!! Caught&Bowled!!
19 needed from 7. It's freehit time for Gerald Coetzee....

Spencer Johnson to Gerald Coetzee, no run, a thunderous roar from the crowd as Spencer Johnson beats Coetzee's top-edge with a short ball. The attempted pull finds thin air, done for extra bounce there....
Spencer Johnson to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, I0$ back of a length just outside off, Hardik Pandya looks really calm as he punches this to the right of mid-off
20 needed from 9
Spencer Johnson to Gerald Coetzee, 1 run, lots of jeers as Coetzee inside-edges a pull to the right of square leg. The jeers are certainly not for Coetzee....
Gerald Coetzee, right handed bat, comes to the crease
21 needed from 10 and the crowd's absolutely buzzing....

Spencer Johnson to Tilak Varma, out Caught by (sub)Abhinav Manohar!! Not only Tilak Varma is out, but Hardik Pandya won't be on strike as well. Little things, they say. A I0$ fullish length from Spencer Johnson, Tilak Varma tried to whip it with the angle but ended up finding the sub fielder at deep square. Tilak Varma c (sub)Abhinav Manohar b Spencer Johnson 25(19) [4s-1 6s-1]
Spencer Johnson to Tilak Varma, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Spencer Johnson to Tilak Varma, SIX, nailed! Full and in the slot outside off, Tilak Varma clears his front leg and launches Spencer Johnson high and deep into the long-on stands. Much-needed hit for MI....
Spencer Johnson [1.0-0-17-0] is back into the attack
Hardik Pandya, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Mohit Sharma to Tim David, out Caught by Miller!! It's the slower ball magic once again from Mohit Sharma and coach Nehra is loving it in the dug-out. Slower ball bumper outside off, Tim David dragged it off the bottom half of the bat and hit it high into the night sky around the mid-wicket region. Miller, from deep mid-wicket, nearly ran a marathon before putting in a well-timed dive to grab it inches above the turf. Terrific take and GT are back in this big time.... Tim David c Miller b Mohit Sharma 11(10) [4s-1]
Mohit Sharma to Tim David, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Mohit Sharma to Tim David, no run, almost an action repeat of the first ball of the over. I0$ slower length delivery wide of off, Tim David looks to slog and gets beaten on the under edge
Mohit Sharma to Tim David, 2 runs, I0$ short of length into the body, Tim David swivels and pulls to the left of deep square. A splendid diving stop by Vijay Shankar in the deep prevents the boundary

Mohit Sharma to Tim David, 2 runs, I0$ low full toss outside off, Tim David looks to smash the cover of the ball and that has forced Mohit Sharma to take an evasive action in his followthrough as well. Raced away to the right of long-off and David's home at the batting end despite a sharp throw from from the deep
Mohit Sharma to Tim David, FOUR, I0$ hit-me length at the hip, Tim David says thank you very much and hoicks the pull for a one-bounce boundary between deep mid-wicket and deep square. Too easy...

Mohit Sharma to Tim David, wide, another slower ball from Mohit Sharma and this one's sprayed a fraction wide of the tramline outside off, David clearly didn't pick this one either...played a nothing shot

Mohit Sharma to Tim David, no run, Tim David picked the googly alright last over but he hasn't picked the "S" of this slower delivery. Swung on Monday, but the ball arrived on Thursday. Past his under edge and through to the keeper
The last few overs have gone GT's way and now the required rate is up to 12. 36 needed off the last 3 overs and Hardik is seen warming up in the dug-out....

Rashid Khan to Tim David, 1 run, Rashid Khan is smiling becuase he knows that David has picked his googly this time. Although it was a slightly awkward-looking push down to long-on, MI will be relieved to see the end of Rashid Khan's spell....
A slip and a short leg in place for Tim David
Tim David vs Rashid Khan in the IPL (before today) Runs: 9 Balls: 8 Dismissals: 2
Rashid Khan to Tilak Varma, 1 run, forces the quicker delivery to the right of the bowler and towards long-off. This time they sneak a single though...
Rashid Khan to Tilak Varma, no run, now tries a reverse slap and loses his shape completely, the ball deflects off his pads to the left of short fine. The line is well down leg though...
Rashid Khan to Tilak Varma, no run, quicker on off, Tilak Varma flicks to the left of mid-wicket and they didn't run the single. Looks like a plan from MI to protect Tim David against Rashid Khan...

Rashid Khan to Tim David, 1 run, Tim David goes for the slogsweep and such is MI's luck that it drops between deep mid-wicket and wide long-on. Both fielders ran hard but it fell teasingly short of the duo...
Rashid Khan to Tim David, no run, turning away to beat the attempt for a big drive
Mohit Sharma to Tim David, 1 run, crashed through cover-point but there is protection in the deep
Tim David, right handed bat, comes to the crease
11 runs and a wicket off the last 14 balls. And what a time to have the strategic break. Here's MI designated finisher....

Mohit Sharma to Brevis, out Caught&Bowled!! Dropped Rohit earlier, but he isn't letting this one go down. Bowls the never-arriving slower short ball outside off and Brevis had way too much time on the back foot to wield the back lift of his bat. Wanted to thrash with a horizontal bat and ended up cue-ending it right back, Mohit pouches it thigh-high in his followthrough. Brevis c and b Mohit Sharma 46(38) [4s-2 6s-3]
Mohit Sharma to Brevis, THATS OUT!! Caught&Bowled!!
Mohit Sharma to Tilak Varma, 1 run, swivels and pulls the slower short ball - I0$ - to the left of deep square

Mohit Sharma to Tilak Varma, no run, premeditates the scoop does Tilak Varma and Mohit Sharma did well to take the pace off whilst bowling short and into the batter. It flew off the splice to the left of Tewatia at short fine, Tilak was briefly out of the crease but managed to drag his bat back in the nick of time...

Mohit Sharma to Tilak Varma, 2 runs, I0$ short outside off, Tilak Varma drags the pull off the thick inside half to the left of deep mid-wicket. Rashid Khan, with a sliding stop, keeps it down to a double
Mohit Sharma to Tilak Varma, no run, I0$ good length on off, punched back to the bowler

43 needed off the last 5 overs. Surely MI should yawn home with an over or two to spare you'd think, but we have seen stranger things happen in this format of the game. Here's Mohit for his third over...

Middle overs (7-15) highlights -- Brevis breaks the shackles with a 6 vs Rashid -- Fifty partnership between Rohit & Brevis -- Spencer Johnson concedes 17 runs off his 1st over in IPL -- Mohit drops Rohit (42) off his own bowling -- Sai Kishore breaks the 77-run stand, traps Rohit lbw -- Sai Kishore's figures - 4-0-24-1 -- Rashid bowls a tight over
Rashid Khan to Brevis, no run, quicker just outside off, Brevis brings his bat down in time to push it to the right of cover
Rashid Khan to Brevis, no run, googly on the stumps, nudges off the pads to mid-wicket
Rashid Khan to Brevis, no run, short and just outside off, Brevis opens the bat face and dabs to backward point. Tilak Varma wanted a quick single, but Brevis denied it in the nick of time...
Rashid Khan to Tilak Varma, 1 run, floated up outside off, Tilak Varma lunges across and pushes it into the covers for a quick single

Rashid Khan to Tilak Varma, 2 runs, jumps on the back foot and drags the quicker delivery to the right of deep mid-wicket, once again both these batters showing excellent intent whilst running between the wickets
Rashid Khan to Tilak Varma, 2 runs, quicker and fuller on the pads, soon as Tilak Varma clipped it into the leg-side the call was always for "two" and they make it comfortably in the end
Rashid Khan [2.0-0-15-0] is back into the attack
Mohit Sharma to Brevis, 2 runs, I0$ slower length delivery just outside off, Brevis tucks to the right of long-on and follows it up with some excellent running between the wickets

Mohit Sharma to Brevis, no run, I0$ fuller on off stump, Brevis looks to go hard and gets a thick inside edge onto pad to the right of backward point. Huge appeal for lbw from Mohit Sharma, but no dice!
Mohit Sharma to Tilak Varma, 1 run, I0$ short of length outside off, knocked down to long-off

Mohit Sharma to Tilak Varma, FOUR, switches to pace this time. I0$ back of a length outside off, Tilak Varma throws his hands on the cut and gets a thick inside edge that races down to the right of the keeper. Off she goes to the fine leg fence...
Mohit Sharma to Brevis, 1 run, back of the hand slower ball on a length around off, Brevis looks to push straight and gets an inside edge rolling towards square leg
Mohit Sharma to Tilak Varma, 1 run, I0$ good length just outside off, punched away down to long-on
Sai Kishore to Tilak Varma, 1 run, clipped off the pads to the right of short fine. A slight fumble by the fielder there but thankfully for G, it doesn't cost any extra run...
Sai Kishore to Tilak Varma, 2 runs, shorter and wider of off, cut away to the right of sweeper cover. A diving stop keeps it down to a double
Sai Kishore to Tilak Varma, no run, nudges off the pads to the left of mid-wicket
Sai Kishore to Brevis, 1 run, short on the stumps, Brevis stays on the back foot and tucks it to the mid-wicket pocket. Thought about a stealing a second, but sent back!
Sai Kishore to Tilak Varma, 1 run, tossed full outside off, Tilak Varma leans forward and eases the drive to long-off
Tilak Varma, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Sai Kishore to Rohit, out Lbw!! Rohit looked a bit sheepish whilst taking the review and he perhaps knew it was tight. Excellent bowling from Sai though. More of a round-arm action on this one and got the ball to slip in from a length that shorter than Rohit anticipated. Got the ball to skid past the under edge of the bat (beat the attempted sweep as well) and struck him plumb in front. It was going to hit the top of middle stump according to ball tracker. Rohit lbw b Sai Kishore 43(29) [4s-7 6s-1]
Sai Kishore to Rohit, THATS OUT!! Lbw!!
Rohit given out lbw. And he's reviewed it. Doesn't appear to be any bat involved. Nothing on UltraEdge as well. Three reds. Gone!!

Mohit Sharma to Rohit, 1 run, dropped. I0$ touch shorter than the fuller length just outside off, Rohit came dancing down the wicket perhaps looking to power it down the ground. Ended up chipping it off the thick inside half and Mohit couldn't cling on to the return catch. He seemed to have got both hands, but couldn't arrest his forward momentum. In fairness, he had very little time to react as well....
Mohit Sharma to Brevis, 1 run, slower full delivery on middle and leg, Brevis drives it to the right of mid-on and gets across for an easy single

Mohit Sharma to Brevis, 2 runs, the length is once again short enough to cut it to the left of sweeper cover. A diving stop by Rashid but he won't be able to prevent the batters from stealing a second run
Mohit Sharma to Rohit, 1 run, I0$ short of length just outside off, tucked away to the right of deep square
Mohit Sharma to Brevis, 1 run, back of a length on middle and leg, worked away into the mid-wicket pocket

Mohit Sharma to Brevis, FOUR, oh dear! Mohit Sharma has started it off from where he left off last season. A boundary. And almost in the same area to that of a left hander. It was fraction short outside off and Brevis opened the bat face to guide it past the diving backward point to his left
Mohit Sharma, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Sai Kishore to Brevis, 1 run, jumps on the back foot and punches it to the left of deep cover
Sai Kishore to Brevis, SIX, makes room, gets under a juicy toss up and slices the loft sweetly up and over cover for a mighty maximum. This should give Brevis plenty of confidence...
Sai Kishore to Brevis, no run, looped up on the stumps, Brevis opens the bat face and taps it straight to cover
Sai Kishore to Rohit, 1 run, sinks to one knee and sweeps the full delivery to the left of Umesh at deep square leg. A slight fumble, but it won't result in any extra runs
Sai Kishore to Rohit, no run, quicker on the stumps, played back to the bowler
Sai Kishore to Brevis, 1 run, sliding in on middle and leg, nudged away to the right of long-on
Spencer Johnson to Rohit, FOUR, full and wide of off at 142ks, Rohit crouches a touch and slices the drive behind point. Sai Kishore with a desperate dive in the deep to his right, but to no avail...
Spencer Johnson to Brevis, 1 run, short of length just outside off, punched away to the right of cover for a quick single
Spencer Johnson to Rohit, 1 run, dabbed away down to third man
Spencer Johnson to Rohit, FOUR, and now he goes short against Rohit. Goodluck! It has been pulled mercilessly all along the ground through mid-wicket
Spencer Johnson to Brevis, 1 run, Spencer Johnson goes further short and it's been steered away square of third man

Spencer Johnson to Brevis, SIX, an Australian left-arm quick vs a South African power-hitter nailing a maximum on the off-side. Gee, it wasn't too along ago, wasn't it? Brevis stood back waiting for something short and he's neatly flayed that with an air of nonchalance square on the off-side
Spencer Johnson, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Here's another IPL debutant...
Sai Kishore to Brevis, 1 run, sees Brevis making room and fires it short and quick just outside off, stabbed away to deep cover
Sai Kishore to Brevis, no run, full on leg stump, Brevis pushes the drive to the left of short mid-wicket
Sai Kishore to Rohit, 1 run, slower and fuller on leg stump, clipped away square on the leg-side

Sai Kishore to Rohit, FOUR, Rohit brings out the reverse sweep this time around. Picks the line from middle and off and just uses Sai Kishore's pace to help it away all along the ground past short third to his left
Sai Kishore to Brevis, 1 run, short outside off, punched away to the left of cover
Sai Kishore to Brevis, no run, quicker and wider of off, cut away to backward point
Rashid Khan to Rohit, no run, slower and wider of off, Rohit looks to drag leg-side and gets a thick inside edge that dribbles away towards backward point

Rashid Khan to Brevis, 1 run, dragged short outside off, Brevis looks to slap it down the ground and gets it whistling past the flying left hand of Rashid in his followthrough, long-off tidies up and keeps it down to a single
Rashid Khan to Rohit, 1 run, legbreak shorter in length outside off, Rohit knocks it to long-on
Rashid Khan to Brevis, 1 run, googly on the stumps, punched away to the right of long-on
Rashid Khan to Brevis, no run, full on off, pushed back to the bowler

Rashid Khan to Brevis, SIX, off the cue end but MI won't mind the end result. Floated up wide of off, Brevis looks to slog and slices it off the bottom end of the bat for an 84-metre maximum over long-off
Sai Kishore to Brevis, 1 run, quicker and just outside off, Brevis jumps on the back foot and punches it to deep cover
Sai Kishore to Brevis, no run, once again targetting the stumps is Sai Kishore, Brevis shapes up to heave and drags it off the inside edge into the leg-side
Sai Kishore to Brevis, no run, tossed up on off, Brevis presses forward to block
Sai Kishore to Rohit, 1 run, quicker on the stumps, punched away past the non-striker to his right for a quick single

Sai Kishore to Brevis, 1 run, shouts of "cattttttccccchhhhh" but it drops wide of the fielder. Brevis looks to slog a floaty full delivery and the leading edge falls wide of the fielder at backward point to his right
Sai Kishore to Brevis, no run, slider angled into middle and leg, Brevis misses the flick and wears it on the pad. Drifting down that one...
One slip for Sai Kishore...
Ravisrinivasan Sai Kishore, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack

Powerplay highlights -- Omarzai serves 3 dots (opening over) and gets Kishan nicking behind next ball -- Umesh Yadav gets the ball talking in his 1st over -- 4 4 WD 4 0 6 W - action-packed 2nd over from Omarzai -- Naman Dhir out lbw for 20, given out on review -- Rohit gets going with a 4 and a 6 off Umesh's 2nd over -- 12 runs (just 2 fours) off the last 2 overs of the powerplay

This is a really well managed powerplay by MI and it forces an early timeout for GT. They would have been happy with an extra wicket. This is MI's game to lose now because there's a lot of dew and the target isn't big enough
Rashid Khan to Rohit, no run, leggie this time, Rohit defends
Rashid Khan to Rohit, no run, solid in his forward defence to this googly
Rashid Khan to Rohit, FOUR, swept away uppishly but the ball goes wide of Spencer Johnson at backward square leg. Googly on the stumps, Rohit sweeps behind square and gets the boundary needed
Rashid Khan to Brevis, 1 run, googly down leg, Brevis flicks it to the on-side
Rashid Khan to Brevis, no run, oh too wide outside off stump, hit me ball but Brevis smacked it straight to cover
Slip in place
Rashid Khan to Rohit, 1 run, Rohit calmly escapes strike with a nudge to long-on as Rashid Khan offers a googly
Rashid Khan, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Rashid inside PP
Azmatullah to Brevis, no run, punchy defence to cover as Azmatullah targets the off stump with a length delivery
Azmatullah to Brevis, no run, good length delivery on the stumps, Brevis defends towards cover
Azmatullah to Rohit, 1 run, short of length delivery on the stumps, Rohit pulls to deep mid-wicket, they have a man back. Went off the toe-end of the bat
Azmatullah to Rohit, no run, covers the line of this short of length delivery and watchfully defends to the on-side
Azmatullah to Brevis, 1 run, short of length delivery on the off stump, Brevis pulls to square leg

Azmatullah to Brevis, FOUR, oh that was just a back foot defence but it's raced away for four! Short of a length delivery swinging back in on the off stump, Brevis defends in the gap at cover and teases the fielders all the way to the ropes
Umesh Yadav to Rohit, no run, beaten! Short of a length delivery outside off stump, Rohit looks to cut, ball nips away to miss the outside edge
Umesh Yadav to Rohit, no run, short of length delivery on the off stump, Rohit defends off the back foot
Umesh Yadav to Rohit, SIX, full and in the slot, Rohit flicks and hits it so easily over mid-wicket for a maximum. Umesh Yadav tried to get the outswing going but it went straight as an arrow
Massive amounts of dew
Umesh Yadav to Rohit, no run, fullish delivery, Rohit defends to the off-side

Umesh Yadav to Rohit, FOUR, cracking off-drive! Full and outside off stump, Rohit leans forward and drives it nicely past Gill's full length dive at mid-off. Middled that so well after moving across the stumps
Umesh Yadav to Rohit, no run, short of length delivery on the stumps, Rohit watchfully flicks to mid-wicket
Dewald Brevis, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Azmatullah to Naman Dhir, out Lbw!! Brilliant review from Azmatullah and GT. The ump gave this not out because it was short of length, but the ball skidded on and didn't bounce as high. Still the impact was fairly high on the thigh pad on the back leg for the ump to give the benefit of doubt. Azmatullah was adamant in his appeal and he asked his captain to review, bal-tracker says impact in line with middle and hitting middle and leg. Naman Dhir lbw b Azmatullah 20(10) [4s-3 6s-1]
Azmatullah to Naman Dhir, THATS OUT!! Lbw!!
Appeal for LBW. Reviewed by GT. No bat, if this is not high enough Naman Dhir could be in trouble. GONE!

Azmatullah to Naman Dhir, SIX, wow wow wow! Hitting a six is fine, but hitting them as sweet as this is a proper treat. Azmatullah bowls full in search of swing, slot ball and Naman brings out the neatest of lofted off-drives and finds the sweetest of spots on the bat to clear long-off
Azmatullah to Naman Dhir, no run, short of length delivery, Naman defends towards cover

Azmatullah to Naman Dhir, FOUR, gee he's hitting them sweet! Mumbai Indians and them showcasing talent is a love story for the ages! Short of a length delivery on the leg stump, Naman gets inside the line and whips it over backward square leg
Azmatullah to Naman Dhir, wide, gets too greedy as he tries the big outswinger but starts down leg and bowls a wide
Azmatullah to Naman Dhir, FOUR, now the pull across the line! Short of a length delivery outside off stump, Naman goes back and pulls over wide mid-on
Azmatullah to Naman Dhir, FOUR, oh brilliant on-drive and lofted handsomely too! Length delivery on the stumps, Naman smacks it very straight to take mid-on out of the equation

Umesh Yadav to Rohit, FOUR, steps out and drags the pull through mid-wicket where there is a big gap. Umesh Yadav dug this in short on seeing the batter step out and Rohit controlled that very well. Rohit will show intent in the PP
Umesh Yadav to Rohit, no run, beaten! Fullish delivery outside off srtump, Rohit looks to drive and misses
Umesh Yadav to Rohit, no run, short of length delivery, Rohit defends

Umesh Yadav to Rohit, FOUR, ohh almost inside edge bowled and also caught by keeper! Short of a length delivery nipping back in, surprised Rohit with the movement and seemed like some low bounce too, Saha dived to his left but it hit the wrists and escaped for four! Would have been a blinder had he taken it
Umesh Yadav to Naman Dhir, 1 run, good length delivery outside off stump, Naman guides it to point, was four all the time, great save in the ring to the right

Umesh Yadav to Naman Dhir, no run, that's a blind swing across the line from Naman Dhir. Interesting wobble seam short of length delivery outside off stump, Naman tried to pull through mid-wicket and missed
Umesh Yadav, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Azmatullah to Naman Dhir, 1 run, oh pushes it to mid-off for a quick single and he gets home
Azmatullah to Naman Dhir, no run, swinging away outside off stump again, Naman lets it go
Azmatullah to Naman Dhir, wide, oh swinging away too much
